#target

Some people tell me I have amazing dedication, or iron willpower. Some people think i'm boring or missing out. None of these are true. What I am, is happy.

Don't you miss chocolate and cake? How do you live without wine at the weekends? Common questions. Firstly, I still eat chocolate, cake, and drink wine. Not in the quantities I used to, but I used to be unhappy. To me I can choose unhealthy and unhappy or I can choose healthiness and happiness. No decision required really.

It took me a year to lose the weight I needed to get to target. It took me another year to realise emotionally and psychologically that I was at target. Because often the emotional side of being overweight is much harder to lose than the weight itself and it took a long time for me to realise the fat girl was gone, and, not coming back! 
I can now fit in size 8 jeans, I can run about with the dogs and not get out of breath, I can get ready to go out without feeling desperately upset. And thanks to @slimmingworld and the support of my amazing group, I have energy, confidence, and a love for life I never had before.

I'm a target member and i'm happy!

I'm always amazed to be asked to do an interview because I still feel like everything is new and everything new is a challenge üò≥ but that means it was *such* an honor to do this interview with fellow NYC planner girl @bettes.pages for @project_kintsugi. We chatted about the importance of food in our lives and in Chinese culture, about the innovation and modernization happening in local Chinatown businesses spearheaded by the sons and daughters and even great great great granddaughters of the immigrant business owners, about dimsum and our many fond memories of it. As Bette wrote, I hope that @wontoninamillion not only makes you smile and reminds you of warm, delicious memories with your family, but that it also encourages you to eat more dimsum as a way of supporting Chinatown and immigrant-owned businesses everywhere. One of my favorite quotes: "An immigrant is an extreme person. No matter how bad circumstances are in your native country, regardless of the death threat, complacency and entropy means most people will stay put amid famine and genocide. Anyone who crosses deserts and mountains and oceans and borders because life means more to him than stillness is brave. Never disrespect an immigrant." (From Elizabeth Wurtzel's "Creatocracy") <3 Without further ado, check out the link in my profile for the full article. Thank you so much to @bettes.pages and @project_kintsugi for the opportunity!! Also, throwback photo! Wearing the original "I'm All A'BAO That Bass" tank üòÜ (I miss my long hair üò¢)

location: {u'slug': u'breaking-bread-bakery', u'id': u'245434648', u'name': u'Breaking Bread Bakery', u'has_public_page': True}
caption:
For the past half-decade, Breaking Bread has been concocting homemade loaves of bread, fresh pastries, croissants, and baked goods, in their spacious bakery overlooking Higuera Street in Downtown SLO!  There are 4-5 artisan breads baked daily, according their weekly Monday through Friday schedule. Today being Thursday, I walked into the aroma of freshly-baked Bordeaux Sourdough, French Baguettes, Honey, and (Baker's Choice) Fig Pecan loaves. 
Turning my attention to their lunch options, I found that they offer Mediterranean, Greek, Power, Cobb, and Chef's salads, in their cold case, made daily with varied greens, vegetables, protein, and toppings, every morning.  What caught my eye was their sandwiches, served on your choice of bread, and also their daily soup offerings.  I opted for a half of the classic BLT, on their Bordeaux Sourdough, and a cup of their Hungarian Cauliflower soup, served with a slice of bread.  Their Honey bread was highly recommended, having just come out of the oven.  I was thoroughly delighted to find it not only still warm, but so flavorful, with just a hint of sweetness from the honey.  The spongy center, combined with crunch of the crust, transported my taste buds back to the Village bakeries I visited in provincial France several years ago.  The soup was seasoned with paprika, and included carrots and a few other vegetables in the broth, along with the cauliflower. 
The 1/2 sandwich is just about $2 less than the whole, which normally goes for $6.91.  The cup of soup, with a slice of bread is $3.94, so my total spend was $9.60.
I couldn't resist and also purchased two of their homemade cookies - a decadent Brown Butter Chocolate Chip and a Ginger Sparkles, with sprinkles of crystallized sugar atop, for $1.25 each.

location: {u'slug': u'bonn-germany', u'id': u'107481562', u'name': u'Bonn, Germany', u'has_public_page': True}
caption:
My newest creation. Sauteed salmon, spelt penne with a creamy sauce and cavolo nero (black cabbage, an italian speciality) with tomato and dry fried peanuts.
I bought the cabbage at the farmer's market today and wanted to use it right away. The cabbage tastes fantastic. Not bitter or too strong. More like a mix of cabbage, turnip greens and spinach. And it stayed crunchy even after blanching. A great meal! And for all of you, who don't like fish: the dish will work with chicken, or without meat at all! üòâ
I blanched the cabbage first, took it out of the water and aside and then cooked the pasta in the same water. That saves space and energy and gives a great taste to the pasta. When the pasta was ready, I poured out the water, readded the cabbage. Then I added the sliced tomato and the peanuts. The sauce was prepared in a different pot and I poured it over the pasta/cabbage, reheated everything and then served it woth the salmon.

My friend, Sithuthukile Mkhwanazi requested that I come and lend her support with something something. Venue #Protea Balalaika #Hotel. Have not been there in over a decade. When the Village Walk was still a place to occasionally check out. Then my buddy Mpho Kgosietsile from Bots happened to be in the same neighbourhood. A little break from work over #dinner was just what the doctor ordered for both of us. Our coy waiter Arnold failed hopelessly at being the #photographer. He tried. So we took over. Catching up. Dinner great. Had a little fun #photoshoot to the amusement of the staff dotted around the #reception area watching us. What to whilst we are waiting for Sthu. 
Then my system turned. Damn. Something that I am #allergic to was in the dinner. The hue of the evening changed. This is why I end up going to the same restaurants where "Everybody knows my name' (Cheers theme song). And most importantly know my dietary requirements. And never cheat by sneaking things in because they think you are just being fussy or forget #food groups! My tolerance levels have plummeted. No wiggle room. Am in agony and discomfort. My poor system has much work to do. Tara, I miss your vigilance about every ingredient that goes into my meal preparations. Needless to say, a real downer ending to a fantastic catch up session with my buddy Mpho. Looking forward to seeing you sooner than later with my two other favourite people. They know who they are. Chia seeds are loaded with nutrients, benefiting your brain and entire body. A single Tbsp. of Chia seeds provides 3g of protein, 3g of healthy fat, and 5g of carbohydrates (all of which comes from fiber). Chia seeds contain calcium, manganese, magnesium, phosphorus, Zinc, potassium, and Vitamins B1, B2, and B3. Chia seeds support healthy bones and may lower the risk of heart disease and type 2 diabetes. The Aztecs and Myans even used chia seeds to fuel performance! (Much better than that sugary sports drink). In addition, chia seeds are high in Omega 3's. However, most of the Omega 3's are in the form of ALA, rather than EPA and DHA
.
Incorporate chia seeds into your diet by mixing them in oats, smoothies, and yogurt. Does anyone else have creative ways they like to eat chia seeds? I'd love to hear. Comment below!

I have changed the recipe, so quick and easy. These are to die for! Orange, Walnut and choc granola bars! Totally healthy and amazing taste! #lowcarb #lowgidiet #unrefinedsugar #healthyfood #cleaneating  #recipe #food #foodie #snacks #granola #oats 
100g butter
3 tbsp golden syrup
85g demerara sugar
140g porridge oat
¬Ω tsp ground cinnamon
50g desiccated coconut
2 tbsp linseeds, slightly crushed 
1 tbsp sesame seeds
2 grated rind of satsuma or tangerine
100g dark choc
100g lightly crushed walnut halves

Heat oven to 160C/fan 140C/gas 3. Butter a 22cm square baking tin, a false bottom works best. Melt the butter, syrup and sugar in a pan. Pour in the oats, cinnamon, coconut, seeds and nuts, orange rind and chocolate , mix and pour into tin. Bake for 30-35 mins. Leave to cool for 10 mins, then cut into squares, I then put in fridge to firm up more for 1 hr. remove from fridge and they should come away and place in airtight container, Will keep for 1 week.

Bahan:
1 lbr puff pastry instan 
Secukupnya pisang matang,potong bulat
Secukupnya keju
Secukupnya meises
1 sdm skm
1 butir kutel,utk olesan

Panaskan oven hingga 200 dercel
Di meja kerja tabur tepung terigu,bentangkan puff pastry,tabur terigu lagi,gilas ringan
Oles skm di tengah sampai rata,tabur meises,tata potongan pisang,tabur meises dan keju

üí•CARDIO OR WEIGHTS?üí• post by@syattfitness
.
#Repost @syattfitness (@get_repost)
„Éª„Éª„Éª
üêôThe fitness industry runs on a pendulum of extremes. Everything is either good or bad. Right or wrong. Healthy or unhealthy. Fattening or fat burning. Issue is, things aren't that black and white. And creating these false dichotomies is what digs us further into fitness "ruts" that are harder and harder to climb out of.
-
üçïCardio is the prime example. For a long time, cardio was *it.* THE thing. Everyone ran or biked or swam or roller skated (lol those were the days) or whatever. Weight lifting was "dangerous," not "functional," and only for "meat heads."
-
üçóRecently, though, this all changed. Nowadays weight lifting is the end-all-be-all of fitness, whereas cardio is hated on and made fun of. Hell, I see coaches every day bragging about how they don't do any cardio whatsoever - only heavy lifting - and stay shredded year round.
-
‚úàÔ∏èAnd that's great. It really is. But there's more to fitness than staying shredded. And just because you don't need to do something to get shredded, doesn't mean it won't help. Nor does it mean there aren't a fistful of other benefits. Truth is, both cardio and weights have a ton of benefits, each of which complement the other.
-
üèìBetween you and me, I don't want to be a one trick pony. Sure, deadlifting 4x my body weight is great. But I also like running a 6min mile. And not getting winded every time I go up a flight of stairs. And, as weird as it sounds, I like finishing a workout out of breath and sweaty and feeling like I just got worked.
-
ü¶ÑFor me, strategically doing both weights and cardio is the best way to get the best of both worlds. So you can be strong as all hell, and the fittest one in the room. You don't have to choose - you can do both.
-

Thursday's üî•Fat lossüî• tip! 
What time of day are you most likely to "give in" or go "off track" with your healthy eating plan?

Is it between lunch and dinner?
Is it when you get home from work?
Is it after dinner when cravings strike?

Recognize your "trouble time" causing you to go off track. 
WHY is this time hard for you? 
Are you not prepared?
Is it true hunger or a craving?
Are you keeping foods in the house that aren't supporting your goals?

MAKE YOUR DIET WORK FOR YOU, not the other way around.

Try this --> *CALORIE PARTITIONING*

Partition your calories to the times of the day when you seem to have increased hunger or desire to eat.

My "trouble time" was in the evenings, which is pretty popular for most. So I make my diet work for me by budgeting and "saving" the load of my daily calorie intake for later in the day when I feel like I need them the most to stay in track with my goals. *Again, this is why it's so IMPORTANT to know, understand, and track your daily calorie intake so you can partition your calories accordingly. 
If you're not assessing, you're guessing.

For me, the most important thing is to go to bed on a full stomach. I sleep better and my compliance to my diet is much greater this way. 
I am fine with feeling a little hunger at times throughout the day, knowing that I can fill that hunger later in the day, look forward to a big meal, and go to bed feeling full and satisfied. This keeps me on track and consistent which leads to the results I'm after.

How do I execute this?

I skip breakfast.
Have my first (smaller) meal around 2pm.
Have a LARGE meal around 7pm.
Have another decent size meal at 10pm.
Go to bed. 
That's my "diet" strategy.

It works for ME, and most importantly... I ENJOY IT. 
And dietary adherence + consistency = results. 
So let's say you're like me, and you also struggle with the evenings. For an example, I have 2,000 calories to work with for my total daily intake if I want to lose fat.

An example of "BAD" calorie partitioning:
*Breakfast: 500 calories
*Snack: 300 calories *Lunch: 600 calories
*Snack: 300 calories *Dinner: .... 300 calories?.... yeah right. *This leaves me with ONLY 300..üëáüèªüëáüèªüëá

caption: THE best barbecued meats at MAM in Notting Hill, the latest venture from Colin Yu of @salvationinnoodles. Focusing on food and techniques from around Hanoi, the star of the show is the barbecued skewers - think smoky, melty pork belly, tender beef wrapped in betel leaf, fresh, juicy king prawns, and lean, tender chicken. They come on a bed of lettuce leaves, shredded carrot, cucumber and pickled red onion, with a zingy, spicy dip and a set of spongy, woven vermicelli wraps to pile it all up in. Gloriously messy to eat and utterly delicious. Don't miss the fish sauce and garlic chicken wings, coated in a crisp outer shell, or the subtle flavour of their in-house pho. caption:
TEQUILA LIME SALMON SALAD
By @thecookierookie üòãüëå
Ingredients
For the Tequila Lime Salmon:
2 salmon filets with skin-on
2 tablespoons olive oil
2 limes, juice and zest
¬º cup tequila
1 (1 oz.) package Old El Paso Taco Seasoning Mix
3 tbsps dark brown sugar
For the Tequila Lime Vinaigrette:
2 tbsps freshly squeezed lime juice
2 tbsps tequila
2 tbsps freshly squeezed orange juice
4 tbsps honey
1 tsp chili powder
¬º cup fresh cilantro, chopped
¬º cup canola oil
For the Salad and Toppings:
¬º head Iceberg lettuce, cleaned and chopped
¬Ω bunch green or red leaf lettuce; cleaned, trimmed & chopped
¬Ω cup chopped fresh tomatoes
¬Ω cup Mexican Blend shredded cheese
1 can black beans, rinsed & drained
1 can sweet corn, rinsed & drained
1 avocado, peeled & sliced or chopped ‚Äì drizzle with lime juice to keep from browning.
¬º cup fresh cilantro, chopped
Tortilla Strips
Instructions
For the Salmon:
(Salmon can be marinated and kept in fridge up to 24 hours prior to cooking.)
Place olive oil, lime juice, lime zest, tequila, Old El Paso Taco Seasoning Mix and brown sugar in a gallon size Ziploc bag and mix until well incorporated. Add the salmon filets and gently rub the marinade over the salmon. Close the bag and marinate it in the fridge 2-24 hours.
When ready to serve, preheat the oven to 425 degrees F. Cover a baking sheet with foil and spray it lightly with nonstick cooking spray.
Remove the salmon from the marinade & place it, skin-side down, on the baking sheet.
Place the baking sheet on the middle rack of the oven & roast it for 4-6 mins per half-inch thickness of salmon. Measure the salmon at the thickest part. 4 mins will give you salmon with a pink center (medium-rare) & 6 mins will be thoroughly cooked through.
The salmon is done when it easily flakes apart with a fork. If desired, test the doneness with an instant read thermometer ‚Äì salmon is considered done at a minimum 145 degrees F at the thickest part of the salmon.
Remove the cooked salmon from the oven & transfer to plate. Remove the skin before placing the salmon on the mixed salad.
For the Salad:

There is no such thing as a universally standard healthy "look." You may be strong, healthy, and of a sound mental state and not look like a fitness model and that's OKAY. Anytime I've ever personally shredded down to the point where I could see a full 6-8 pack I was doing so like it was a full time job. That amount of time and energy and discipline is certainly commendable but just because you aren't applying the maximum human effort possible does not mean you are unhealthy in any way. I say this all the time, but remember this is your life and you get to choose your experiences. People not never understand your personal battles, your injuries, your allergies, your health conditions, or your circumstances that got you to where you are at this current moment. Be kind to yourself, be patient with yourself, and don't get caught up in comparing yourself. Keep on keeping on üôåüôåüôå

üéØ DAY SEVEN - BREAKFAST - Quick Banana Pancakes üçå
Week One done! While physical changes are yet to be revealed, I'm definitely feeling lighter, healthier and happier - I'm in control of my body and what I'm putting into it. This morning it was these easy banana pancakes - 5 ingredients; 5 minutes to prep and 5 minutes to cook.
Recipe:
Blend 1 mashed banana, a pinch of baking powder, a pinch or two of aromatic spice (I used clove but you can use cinnamon, star anise, nutmeg, etc), a pinch of salt and one egg. Blend for about 3-5 seconds (you want it smooth, but not thinned out). Pour into an oiled pan and flip when bubbles appear. I was in a rush this morning but it would have been deeeelish with raspberries and peanut butter!

I get asked a lot "What do you eat?" . . . . 
A better question would be "How do you eat?" . . . 
The truth is you can eat whatever you want as long as the quantity of those foods are within your personal allowance of protein, carbs and fats (macronutrients) and in accordance with your fitness goals you are looking to achieve.

The way you go about moderating these foods is to track them throughout the day using a calorie counting app such as myfitnesspal that way you can allow for the foods you personally want to eat whilst staying on track with your fitness goals.

Want to quickly get lean? Ditch the carbs. Check out these Grilled Chicken Caesar Wraps ‚ù§Ô∏è
.
By @cleanfoodcrush
.
makes about 8-10 wraps/4-5 servings 
Ingredients:
1 Head Romaine Lettuce 
1.2 lbs. Chicken Tenders 
1.5 cups Cherry Tomatoes, sliced
1/4 Cup Parmesan Cheese ‚Äì grated 
1 Tbs. Garlic Powder 
1 Tbs. Italian Seasoning 
Sea Salt and Pepper to taste 
Avocado Oil, or Olive Oil 
Greek Yogurt Caesar Dressing:
Juice from 1 fresh lemon 
2 Tbsp soy sauce, or coconut aminos 
1 Tbsp raw honey 
1 Tsp dijon mustard 
1/2 cup Greek yogurt 
Instructions:
Whisk all dressing ingredients together until combined and smooth. 
Keep refrigerated until ready to serve. 
Sprinkle chicken tenders with garlic powder, Italian seasoning, sea salt and pepper - rub to coat evenly.
Preheat a large grill pan or outdoor grill over medium-high heat. rub grill with 2 Tbsp. oil.
Grill the chicken for about 4-5 minutes on each side, or until cooked through. 
Prepare 8-10 large leaves of romaine lettuce. 
Once the chicken has cooked and cooled, add a couple of tenders to each romaine leave. Then top with a few cherry tomatoes, drizzle

Nyobain masak Beef Yakiniku nih üòä ini pake resep chicken yakiniku by @dee_devina tapi aku ganti pake daging sapi + masaknya juga aku adjust sama selera sendiri yaa dan beneran deh rasanya ini enakk banget, wanginya juga enakk üòç thankyou ya dee udh sharing resep + cara masaknya yg detail bgt gini @dee_devina üôèüèª
.
Beef Yakiniku ala @silvialim18
.
Bumbu untuk marinate:
1 sdm kecap asin
1/2 sdm saus tiram
1/2 sdm kecap manis
Merica bubuk sesuai selera
.
Bahan:
250 gr daging sapi has dalam, iris tipis
3 siung bawang putih, cincang halus
1 bh bawang bombay, iris2
3 bh cabe rawit merah, iris2
1 sdm kecap inggris
1 sdm minyak wijen
1 sdt gula pasir
150 ml air panas
1 sdm tepung sagu/maizena
.
Steps:
1. Marinate irisan daging sapi dgn bumbu marinate. Biarkan kurleb 15 menit, setelah itu berikan 1 sdm tepung sagu/maizena, aduk rata.
2. Panaskan teflon hingga cukup panas, masukkan sdikit minyak lalu tumis bawang putih hingga wangi. Setelah itu masukkan irisan daging sapi, masak dan aduk2 hingga berubah warna. Masukkan minyak wijen+kecap inggris+gula, biarkan mendidih sbntar lalu aduk cepat. 
3. Diamkan dagingnya sbntar sperti saat panggang daging di teflon, lalu tambahkan irisan bwg bombay+rawit merahnya, aduk rata.
4. Terakhir masukkan air panas, masak hingga mendidih, icip dan koreksi rasanya. Masak hingga air sedikit susut. Angkat dan sajikan.
